      "content": "wait, \"the only interpretation that aligns\"? that's a pretty huge claim. aren't there lots of legal scholars who argue that the founders were talking about a \"well regulated militia\" and that the current court is basically just making up new rules to fit a modern political agenda? why is originalism the only valid way to look at it?",
